<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910501-0103</DOCNO><DOCID>910501-0103.</DOCID><HL>   Heilig-Meyers to Offer Shares</HL><DATE>05/01/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   HMY</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>OTHER SPECIALTY RETAILERS OF LIMITED PRODUCT LINES (OTS)STOCK AND BOND REGISTRATIONS, PRICINGS (REG)ALL SPECIALTY RETAILERS (RTS)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)</IN><NS>BOND AND STOCK REGISTRATIONS AND PRICINGS (REG)STOCK andamp; OTHER MARKET NEWS (STK)</NS><RE>VIRGINIA (VA)</RE><LP>   RICHMOND, Va. -- Heilig-Meyers Co. plans to issue twomillion new common shares, with 1.6 million to be offered inthe U.S. and the remainder overseas.   Based on current market price, the offering is expected toraise about $56 million, part of which will go to retiringsome of the company's $81.9 million in short-term debt. Aspokesman for the furniture retailer said the proceeds alsowill help it be prepared for growth.</LP><TEXT>   The offering, which will increase the company's sharesoutstanding to 12.6 million, will be underwritten both in theU.S. and abroad by a group led by Goldman, Sachs andamp; Co. Theunderwriters have an over-allotment option of 300,000 shares.   In composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange,Heilig-Meyers's shares fell 37.5 cents to $27.875.</TEXT></DOC>